      <description>&lt;div style=&#34;position:relative; clear:both; padding:0;&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;img src=&#34;https://duragauge.github.io/img/chapter-2/skydive.jpg&#34;  title=&#34;Photo from the US Air Force on Flickr&#34;  alt=&#34;Photo from the US Air Force on Flickr&#34; style=&#34;display:block; width:100%; height:auto;&#34; &gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;span style=&#34;position:absolute; height:auto; bottom:0em; right:0em; margin:0;  padding: .1em .3em;  color:white;  font-size: .8em;  background:rgba(0, 0, 0, 1);  text-align:right;  z-index:5;  opacity:0.65;  border-radius:.3em 0em 0em 0em;&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;a href = &#34;https://flic.kr/p/cecNKQ&#34;&gt;Photo from the US Air Force on Flickr&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;br&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;introduction&#34;&gt;Introduction&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Do skydivers fall at a constant speed or do they go faster and faster the longer they fall?  Is there anything they can do to control their speed or is it completely out of their hands?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
